  "prompt": "How do I become a biotechnology entrepreneur?",
  "response": "To become a biotechnology entrepreneur, follow these steps:\n\n1. Educational Background\n- Obtain a relevant degree (Biology, Biotechnology, Biochemistry, Bioengineering)\n- Consider advanced degrees like PhD or MBA\n- Pursue specialized courses in entrepreneurship\n\n2. Develop Technical Skills\n- Stay updated on latest biotechnology trends\n- Learn laboratory techniques\n- Understand research methodologies\n- Gain expertise in specific biotechnology domains\n\n3. Build Business Knowledge\n- Take entrepreneurship classes\n- Learn about business planning\n- Understand intellectual property laws\n- Study market analysis and commercialization strategies\n\n4. Gain Practical Experience\n- Work in biotechnology research labs\n- Participate in internships\n- Collaborate with startups\n- Attend industry conferences\n- Network with professionals\n\n5. Develop Business Skills\n- Learn fundraising techniques\n- Understand venture capital\n- Develop pitch presentation skills\n- Learn financial management\n- Practice strategic planning\n\n6. Identify Innovative Ideas\n- Recognize market gaps\n- Develop unique solutions\n- Consider potential commercial applications\n- Focus on solving significant problems\n\n7. Build Professional Network\n- Connect with investors\n- Join biotechnology associations\n- Attend startup events\n- Collaborate with research institutions\n\n8. Secure Funding\n- Apply for grants\n- Seek venture capital\n- Consider angel investors\n- Explore government funding opportunities\n\nPersistence, continuous learning, and adaptability are key to success.",
